[[C1641249569|Learn how to include custom indexers]].

A custom indexer class must be implemented in accordance with this template:

<syntaxhighlight lang="Ruby">
# dataspects-indexing-service/lib/indexers/YourIndexerClasses/your_first_indexer.rb
class YourFirstIndexer < Dataspects::Indexer

  def initialize
    @profilesURL = 'lib/indexers/YourIndexerClasses/profiles.yml' # `pwd` here is dataspects-indexing-service/
    @elasticsearchClusterLabel = 'elasticsearchlocal'             # The label refers to an entry in @profiles
    @indexName =
    super                                                         # Dataspects::Indexer.initialize provides @elasticsearchCluster and @profiles
  end

  def store_to_index(document)                                    # Called dataspects-indexing-service/app/controllers/document_controller.rb

  end

end
</syntaxhighlight>

